               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360404-name-1310" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1310" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1310" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was at Greenwich fair on Tues<lb></lb>day the 15th of April—I saw the prisoner in company together for three-quarters of an hour—I saw Johnson attempt four different person pockets—Smith was standing near him, apparently to hide him—Johnson took handkerchief from prosecutor's pocket—I touched the prosecutor on the shoulder, and immediately collared the two prisoners, and Johnston then threw the handkerchief down—I picked it up, and the gentleman came to the station-house—they were close together when they attempted the pockets.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360404-name-1311" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1311" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1311" type="surname" value="M'DONALD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1311" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>DAVID M'DONALD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a tailor. I was at the fair—a person touched me on the shoulder, and said I had lost my handkerchief—I immediately for, and missed it—he picked it off the ground, and produced it—the two prisoners were next to me at the time.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183604040238"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Smith's Defence</hi>. I never saw this man before, and never touched the handkerchief.</p>
